				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">My Pet Peeve<a name="47645"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 22 04 5:58 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>People who won't talk with you if they have issues with you, but will talk to just about anyone else and making those people promise not to tell the person it is about.
<br />

<br />
Talk about a bunch of bovine fecal matter!
<br />

<br />
If you have issues with someone take the time to talk with them.  PM off line is best if you really have issues.  Just don't swear and such.  Send a concise and well written note on what they are doing that has you upset with them.  Don't worry if you think they are going to take it bad; things are bad already.
<br />

<br />
Many issues can be resolved if you take the time to work it out.  Ignoring the problem doesn't make it go away.  Ignoring it makes it fester and grow and blow up like a big ugly  gross zit.
<br />

<br />
So, if you have issues with someone, deal with it by communicating with the person(s), please! <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-12.gif" border="0" alt="Mad" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
PS.  I've had one guild totally destroyed by such things, and another one come close to destruction.  Neither had to go there. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-6.gif" border="0" alt="Sad" hspace="2" /></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
