				<td colspan="2"><span>Word.
<br />
I had an ex-girlfriend who lost her job over something like this.
<br />

<br />
A coworker became uncomfortable with her over personal reasons. (IMO, it was his problem, not hers.) Instead of talking to her about it, he went to the boss and said that he wasn't comfortable working alongside her but refused to explain why, just kept insisting that he be transferred to a different department.
<br />

<br />
He was transferred, all right... but she was fired. It turned out that he and a couple of his buddies had been complaining about my ex for weeks, behind her back.
<br />

<br />
While this sounds like my ex was a really obnoxious person, that wasn't really it. Without going to in excrutiating detail, it could have been fixed had they talked to her directly rather than gossip behind her back to the boss.</span></td>
