				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: My Pet Peeve<a name="48564"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 27 04 11:50 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>If she was &quot;fired&quot; she has a strong suit angainst her previous employer, especially if there weren't any meetings between her and her boss to discuss the matters at hand. 
<br />
However, if she was &quot;laid off&quot; she might not have a leg to stand on in court.  There is an annoying employment status known as &quot;at will employment&quot; which allows the employee or employer to terminate employment at anytime without reason and most employers are hiring people under this status.  The reasoning behind having this around was so that employers could take care of sexual harrasment and other abuse type cases quickly and without fear of rebutle from the employee.  It's very problematic in that employers also use this to get rid of people for what ever reason plagues them that day.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
